Thomson Reuters Currency Trading System Is Disrupted, WSJ Says

-- B y   A l a n   P u r k i s s
-- 
2011-03-09T10:59:14Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-09/thomson-reuters-currency-trading-system-is-disrupted-wsj-says.html
Disruption at  Thomson Reuters
Corp. (TRI) ’s currency trading system affected trades in Australian
and New Zealand dollars and in the British pound today, the Wall
Street Journal reported, citing several unidentified traders.  Thomson Reuters wasn’t immediately available for comment,
the newspaper said, adding that it wasn’t clear when a normal
service would be resumed.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Alan Purkiss at 
 apurkiss@bloomberg.net  